val kings of Norway, including  Magnus I  (  1024–47 ), known as Magnus the Good, and  Magnus VI  (  1238–80 ), known as Magnus the Law Mender. There are several early Scandinavian saints called Magnus, including an earl of  Orkney  (  d. 1116 ), to whom Kirkwall cathedral is dedicated. The name was imported to Scotland and Ireland during the Middle Ages."],"variants":[{"name":"Mànas","meanings":["Gaelic equivalent of   Magnus ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":22,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Dame Agnus de Vernon was born about 1360, in Shipbrook, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Sir William de Atherton II about 1637, in Cheshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died on 29 December 1414, in Leigh, Lancashire, England, at the age of 55."},"et":{"circa 1360–29 December 1414":"umbes 1360–29. detsember 1414","1347–1416":"1347–1416","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","1384–1417":"1384–1417","1387–Male":"1387–Surnud","1360–1414":"1360–1414","29 December 1414":"29. detsember 1414","1384":"1384","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","circa 1387":"umbes 1387","1414":"1414","1347":"1347","circa 1360":"umbes 1360","1387":"1387","1417":"1417","about 1384":"umbes 1384","1416":"1416","Atherton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Atherton, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Atherton, Lancashire, England":"Atherton, Lancashire, England","Shipbrook, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Shipbrook, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Leigh, Lancashire, England":"Leigh, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"circa 